      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(plugins): add Control UI entry points",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: Plugins can expose gateway-authenticated HTTP routes, but there was no generic way for a plugin to register a first-class Control UI navigation entry.\n- What changed: Added generic Plugin UI Entry Points across the plugin registry, gateway protocol, launch-token plumbing, and Control UI navigation/rendering.\n- Security follow-up: Plugin UI entry registration, launch/session auth, and iframe bridge proxying now validate canonical decoded plugin roots, so encoded dot-segment paths cannot let one plugin UI session authorize sibling plugin routes.\n- Scope boundary: This PR does not add the Session Search plugin or any plugin-specific UI. The proof plugin lives separately on [`Ittiz/openclaw@forge/session-search-plugin`](https://github.com/Ittiz/openclaw/tree/forge/session-search-plugin).\n\n## Working Example Plugin\n\nThe working example is the Session Search plugin on the plugin-only proof branch:\n\n- Branch: [`Ittiz/openclaw@forge/session-search-plugin`](https://github.com/Ittiz/openclaw/tree/forge/session-search-plugin)\n- README: [`README.md`](https://github.com/Ittiz/openclaw/blob/forge/session-search-plugin/README.md)\n- Entry point registration: [`index.ts`](https://github.com/Ittiz/openclaw/blob/forge/session-search-plugin/index.ts)\n- Manifest: [`openclaw.plugin.json`](https://github.com/Ittiz/openclaw/blob/forge/session-search-plugin/openclaw.plugin.json)\n\nThat branch intentionally contains only plugin files, not the OpenClaw source tree.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Current head tested: `23fe820d30319b9ec40a5470c2e562d78c301373`.\n- Behavior addressed: Plugin UI entry points can be listed/launched/rendered, and decoded/canonicalized plugin paths remain confined to the owning plugin root across registration, launch/session auth, and sandbox bridge/proxy requests.\n- Real environment tested: local Linux checkout after rebasing on current `main`, Vitest gateway/UI/plugin contract shards, plugin SDK surface checker, and oxlint.\n\nCommands run after the current fix:\n\n```bash\ngit diff --check\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/plugin-host-hooks.test.ts src/gateway/server.plugin-http-auth.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/host-hooks.contract.test.ts ui/src/ui/navigation.browser.test.ts ui/src/ui/navigation.test.ts ui/src/ui/open-external-url.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/schema-normalization-runtime-contract.test.ts --reporter=verbose\nnode scripts/plugin-sdk-surface-report.mjs --check\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/navigation.browser.test.ts --reporter=verbose\nnode scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs --threads=8\n```\n\nEvidence:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ... --reporter=verbose\n[test] passed 4 Vitest shards in 91.89s\n\n$ node scripts/plugin-sdk-surface-report.mjs --check\npackage-exported forbidden subpaths: 0\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/navigation.browser.test.ts --reporter=verbose\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  17 passed (17)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 9.84s\n\n$ node scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs --threads=8\n[oxlint:core] finished\n[oxlint:extensions] finished\n[oxlint:scripts] finished\n```\n\nSpecific regression locked in:\n\n- `src/gateway/server.plugin-http-auth.test.ts` rejects Plugin UI Entry Point sessions when decoded path candidates leave the plugin root.\n- `src/plugins/contracts/host-hooks.contract.test.ts` rejects encoded dot-segment sibling escapes at entry-point registration.\n- `ui/src/ui/navigation.test.ts` rejects external, contextual, cross-plugin, and encoded sibling paths.\n- `ui/src/ui/navigation.browser.test.ts` verifies sandboxed in-app plugin requests are proxied only for plugin-owned paths and replies use a same-origin frame target.\n\n## Security Impact\n\n- New permissions/capabilities? Yes. Plugins can expose Control UI entry points.\n- Secrets/tokens handling changed? Yes. Entry-point launch uses short-lived Plugin UI launch/session tokens.\n- Data access scope changed? Yes. Entry points declare required operator scopes.\n- Mitigation: Entry-point paths are constrained to canonical plugin-owned roots; launch/session auth and iframe proxying reject decoded sibling escapes; direct unauthenticated plugin route access remains blocked.\n\n## Compatibility / Migration\n\n- Backward compatible? Yes.\n- Config/env changes? No.\n- Migration needed? No.\n",
